text: Robin Nelisse (born January 25, 1978 in Rotterdam, Netherlands) is a former Dutch football player. ==Career == He began his professional career at Feyenoord Rotterdam in 1997. he came to the first team from Rotterdam's U19 team. In 1999 he became Dutch champion as a substitute player. Then he moved to Cambuur Leeuwarden in 1999, where he worked for a year before moving to AZ Alkmaar. After five years in Alkmaar, he moved to FC Utrecht . 2008 he moved to Austria to FC Red Bull Salzburg. He celebrated his first goal in his first Bundesliga match against SV Mattersburg on 9 July 2008. On 20 January 2011, the player and the club agreed to terminate the contract. On 11 August 2011, he announced that he was ending his career due to knee problems. ==International == He played for the Netherlands Antilles. He made his debut against Nicaragua on 6 February 2008.
